Description:
    Generates a complete DDD stack (entity, record, migration, repository,
    service, endpoint) for every resource defined in an IR JSON file.

    IR (Intermediate Representation) is a language-agnostic JSON format
    that describes API resources — their attributes, types, permitted
    fields, and CRUD operations. See docs/ddd-ir-schema.md for the
    full specification.

Usage:
    rails generate from_ir PATH_TO_IR_JSON

Examples:
    # Generate from default location
    rails generate from_ir docs/ir.json

    # Generate from custom path
    rails generate from_ir api/schema.json

    # Dry run — see what would be generated
    rails generate from_ir docs/ir.json --pretend

IR File Format:
    {
      "$schema": "ddd-ir/1.0",
      "resources": [
        {
          "name": "Post",
          "plural": "posts",
          "path": "/posts",
          "attributes": {
            "id":         { "type": "integer", "nullable": false, "readonly": true },
            "title":      { "type": "string",  "nullable": true,  "readonly": false },
            "body":       { "type": "text",    "nullable": true,  "readonly": false },
            "published":  { "type": "boolean", "nullable": true,  "readonly": false },
            "created_at": { "type": "datetime","nullable": false, "readonly": true },
            "updated_at": { "type": "datetime","nullable": false, "readonly": true }
          },
          "permit": ["title", "body", "published"],
          "operations": [
            { "action": "index",   "method": "GET",    "path": "/posts" },
            { "action": "show",    "method": "GET",    "path": "/posts/{id}" },
            { "action": "create",  "method": "POST",   "path": "/posts" },
            { "action": "update",  "method": "PATCH",  "path": "/posts/{id}" },
            { "action": "destroy", "method": "DELETE",  "path": "/posts/{id}" }
          ],
          "validators": []
        }
      ]
    }

Workflow:
    1. Write ir.json by hand, or generate from existing app: rake ddd:ir
    2. Run: rails generate from_ir docs/ir.json
    3. Run migrations: rails db:migrate
    4. Add routes: endpoint PostsEndpoint
    5. Generate OpenAPI docs: rake ddd:emit[openapi]
